<h1 id="6-slurm">6. <a href="https://github.com/mattthias/slurm">slurm</a></h1>
<p>Slurm is ‚Äúmore‚Äù another network load monitor that shows device statistics along with an ASCII graph. It supports 3 different styles of graphs, each of which can be activated using the keys c, s and l. Simple in resources, slurm no longer displays details about the network load.</p>

<p>Installation example on a Linux distro:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge slurm <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>slurm <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Mint, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> slurm <span class="c"># Arch, Manjaro, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>dnf <span class="nb">install </span>slurm <span class="c"># Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora, ...</span></code></pre></figure>

<p><img src="/assets/img/network/slurm.png" alt="slurm" /></p>

<p>Example of use:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">slurm <span class="nt">-s</span> <span class="nt">-i</span> eth0</code></pre></figure>

