<h1 id="16-ifstat">16. <a href="https://github.com/Yamagi/ifstat">ifstat</a></h1>
<p>Ifstat reports the network bandwidth in a batch style mode. The output is in an easy format to record and analyze using other programs or utilities.</p>

<p>Installation example on a Linux distro:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerges ifstat <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>ifstat <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Mint, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> ifstat <span class="c"># Arch, Manjaro, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>dnf <span class="nb">install </span>ifstat <span class="c"># Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora, ...</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Example of use:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">ifstat <span class="nt">-t</span> <span class="nt">-i</span> eth0 0.5
  Time           eth0
HH:MM:SS   KB/s <span class="k">in  </span>KB/s out
09:59:21      2.62      2.80
09:59:22      2.10      1.78
09:59:22      2.67      1.84
09:59:23      2.06      1.98
09:59:23      1.73      1.79</code></pre></figure>

